00:02:08.715 --> 00:02:10.076
just a touch.

00:02:10.676 --> 00:02:12.519
So it's a little more like a letter.

00:02:12.639 --> 00:02:15.921
But what we used was the primarily...

00:02:17.591 --> 00:02:20.274
that led tablet from the Exodus,

00:02:20.294 --> 00:02:22.895
so it dates back to the fourteenth century

00:02:23.477 --> 00:02:23.956
BCE.

00:02:24.276 --> 00:02:26.199
It was right at the conclusion of the

00:02:26.258 --> 00:02:26.620
Exodus,

00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:29.301
and it had so many of the letters,

00:02:29.502 --> 00:02:33.045
and some of these letters were presented

00:02:33.186 --> 00:02:36.288
very differently than what we had seen in

00:02:36.308 --> 00:02:38.450
the old text that we had been using.

00:02:39.521 --> 00:02:40.882
And so we just tried to update it

00:02:40.962 --> 00:02:42.002
for that purpose.

00:02:42.763 --> 00:02:45.383
And the old text was not professionally

00:02:45.424 --> 00:02:45.924
created,

00:02:46.304 --> 00:02:48.965
which means that the heights of the

00:02:49.004 --> 00:02:49.344
letters,

00:02:49.384 --> 00:02:51.466
the widths of the letters were wildly

00:02:51.526 --> 00:02:52.306
inconsistent.

00:02:52.325 --> 00:02:54.507
The spacing between letters was wildly

00:02:54.567 --> 00:02:55.287
inconsistent.

00:02:55.526 --> 00:02:57.008
Just a whole lot of things that made

00:02:57.048 --> 00:02:59.389
it exceedingly difficult to use.

00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:00.609
If you used a space bar,

00:03:00.868 --> 00:03:02.330
you'd go halfway across the page.

00:03:03.371 --> 00:03:04.852
And so every time I would use it,

00:03:04.891 --> 00:03:08.075
I would be presenting one letter in an

00:03:08.216 --> 00:03:10.258
eight point and the next letter in

00:03:10.359 --> 00:03:11.079
fourteen point.

00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:13.262
So they would work well together.

00:03:14.383 --> 00:03:16.224
So they were just in completely different

00:03:16.265 --> 00:03:16.586
styles.

00:03:16.645 --> 00:03:19.750
So we we spent a couple of weeks

00:03:19.789 --> 00:03:21.290
studying everything we could find.

00:03:22.051 --> 00:03:24.493
terms of old scripts there actually is an

00:03:24.554 --> 00:03:27.074
Egyptian script that's very similar to it

00:03:27.115 --> 00:03:28.735
there's a Phoenician script that's quite

00:03:28.776 --> 00:03:31.657
similar a Moabite script that's similar

00:03:32.799 --> 00:03:35.901
and of course old traces of a hebrew

00:03:35.941 --> 00:03:38.163
script all the same alphabet obviously

00:03:38.242 --> 00:03:40.903
same twenty two letters all drawn

00:03:41.284 --> 00:03:42.846
remarkably similar so we just tried to

00:03:43.145 --> 00:03:45.866
update them for what we had had seen

00:03:46.568 --> 00:03:48.348
